 degree in history and geography. \nIn 1928, Weulersse received the last Autour Du Monte travel scholarship that was financed by a foundation funded by Albert Kahn, a banker.<ref>{{cite web |URL=https://journals.openedition.org/cybergeo/24203 |title=Professorial patronage and the formation of French geographical knowledge... |publisher=openedition.org |accessdate=December 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 1941, Weulersse obtained his Doctorate of Letters.\n\n== Career ==\nWeulersse became a professor at [[Chartres]], and at [[Lyc\u00e9e Condorcet]].\n\nIn 1943, Weulersse became a master of colonial geography at [[Aix-Marseille University]].<ref name=\"article\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn August 28, 1946, Weulersse died in [[Dakar]], Senegal.\n\n== Works ==\n* ''Le pays des Alaouites'', Th\u00e8se, Tours, Arrault, 1940, 2 volumes, 422 p. \n* ''Noirs et Blancs. A travers l'Afrique nouvelle de Dakar au Cap'', Paris, Armand Colin, 1931, 242 p. (Re-printed 1993, Paris)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Albert Kahn (banker)]] - provider of travelling scholarship.\n* [[Maurice Le Lannou]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Additional sources ==\n*{{cite book|last=M\u00e2eouchy|first=Nadine|last2=Sluglett|first2=Peter|title=Les Mandats fran\u00e7ais et anglais dans une perspective comparative|publisher=BRILL|year=2004|isbn=9789004133136}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://photographesenoutremerafrique.blogspot.com/2009/11/weulersse-j.html?m=1 Weulersse, Jacques at photographesenoutremerafrique.blogspot.com] (in French)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:French geographers]]\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1946 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix          = \n| name                      = Jacques Weulersse\n| honorific_suffix          = \n| native_name               = \n| native_name_lang          = \n| image                     = <!-- just the name, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| image_