1941, Weulersse obtained his Doctorate of Letters.\n\n== Career ==\nWeulersse became a professor at [[Chartres]], and at [[Lyc\u00e9e Condorcet]].\n\nIn 1943, Weulersse became a master of colonial geography at [[Aix-Marseille University]].<ref name=\"article\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn August 28, 1946, Weulersse died in [[Dakar]], Senegal.\n\n== Works ==\n* ''Le pays des Alaouites'', Th\u00e8se, Tours, Arrault, 1940, 2 volumes, 422 p. \n* ''Noirs et Blancs. A travers l'Afrique nouvelle de Dakar au Cap'', Paris, Armand Colin, 1931, 242 p. (Re-printed 1993, Paris)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Albert Kahn (banker)]] - provider of travelling scholarship.\n* [[Maurice Le Lannou]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Additional sources ==\n*{{cite book|last=M\u00e2eouchy|first=Nadine|last2=Sluglett|first2=Peter|title=Les Mandats fran\u00e7ais et anglais dans une perspective comparative|publisher=BRILL|year=2004|isbn=9789004133136}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://photographesenoutremerafrique.blogspot.com/2009/11/weulersse-j.html?m=1 Weulersse, Jacques at photographesenoutremerafrique.blogspot.com] (in French)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:French geographers]]\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1946 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life:Typo fixing, replaced: In August 28, 1946 \u2192 On August 28, 1946", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacques_Weulersse"}
